results.occurrenceRemarks: Found with Argentina Ants. Skinks seem to do well in this area despite the presence of the Ants. This one was found partially buried in the loomy soil with the ants, the sandy/loomy soil type may have something to do with the survival of the skinks thriving despite the ants in this area.  Just a Theory, based on the high number of observations, in sandy/soft soil types vs clay and other coastal soils
